  "prompt": "Which is the best DSLR under 2500?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, there are several great DSLR options available under $2500, depending on your specific needs such as photography style, features, and preferences. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Canon EOS 90D**\n   - 32.5 MP APS-C sensor\n   - Dual Pixel Autofocus\n   - 4K video recording\n   - Good battery life\n   - Versatile for both photography and video\n\n2. **Nikon D7500**\n   - 20.9 MP APS-C sensor\n   - Excellent low-light performance\n   - 8 fps continuous shooting\n   - 4K UHD video\n   - Good build quality\n\n3. **Nikon D5600**\n   - 24.2 MP APS-C sensor\n   - 39-point autofocus system\n   - Good for beginners\n   - Vari-angle touchscreen\n   - Built-in Wi-Fi and Bluetooth\n\n4. **Canon EOS Rebel T8i (EOS 850D)**\n   - 24.1 MP APS-C sensor\n   - Dual Pixel AF with 45 AF points\n   - 4K video capability\n   - User-friendly for beginners\n   - Vari-angle touchscreen\n\n5. **Sony Alpha a68**\n   - 24.2 MP APS-C sensor\n   - 79-point autofocus system\n   - 8 fps continuous shooting\n   - Good image stabilization\n   - Great for sports and action photography\n\nWhen choosing a DSLR, consider factors like ergonomics, lens availability, and whether you need features like 4K video or advanced autofocus capabilities. Prices can fluctuate, so checking for sales or special offers is a good idea.",
